Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    # Update package list and install required software
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        procps \
        --no-install-recommends
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the assessment framework
    pip install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Ensure the default working directory for the student exists and is writable
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 0777 /home/user     # Allow any non-root user to create artifacts here

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Standard PATH setup; do NOT override $HOME
    export PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:$PATH

%labels
    Author="Incident Response Exercise Image"
    Description="Base image for CPU snapshot task. Contains Python, pytest, and a writable /home/user."

%help
This container provides the runtime environment for the “CPU-intensive process
snapshot” incident-response exercise.

Key points:
• Python 3 and pytest are installed for automated grading.
• /home/user exists and is world-writable so the learner can create required
  artifacts.
• The ir_logs directory and top_cpu.log file are intentionally **absent**; the
  student must create them per the task instructions.